Project Name: Doooda

Doooda is a secure SaaS web application for writers.
The system is built around a single shared backend that serves:
- Web application (primary writing experience)
- Mobile applications (Android & iOS companion apps)

Core principles (non-negotiable):
- One source of truth for all data (users, projects, chapters, scenes)
- Web and mobile must share the same authentication system
- No duplicate business logic across platforms
- All user-generated content must be persistent and never auto-modified

Technical constraints:
- Supabase is used for authentication, database, and storage
- Row Level Security (RLS) is enforced on all user-owned data
- Backend functions must be secure and deterministic
- Sensitive data and tokens must never be exposed to the client

Product philosophy:
- Doooda empowers writers to stay in control
- The system assists but never overrides creative decisions
- Simplicity, clarity, and trust are more important than feature volume

Important:
- New features must not break existing user data
- Backward compatibility is required
- Stability and data safety are higher priority than speed of development